00:04:41.208 --> 00:04:41.813
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:41.813 --> 00:04:42.730
DE'ARRA TAYLOR: Ashes.

00:04:42.730 --> 00:04:44.660
KEN WALKER: So I want to ask--

00:04:44.660 --> 00:04:45.940
Madea came out so long ago.

00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:46.310
TYLER PERRY: Yeah.

00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:47.435
KEN WALKER: At what point--

00:04:47.435 --> 00:04:49.370
I guess, long ago
that you decided

00:04:49.370 --> 00:04:51.350
Madea is going to be
Madea, but not only that,

00:04:51.350 --> 00:04:53.190
I'm going to play Madea?

00:04:53.190 --> 00:04:54.690
TYLER PERRY: Two
things happened.

00:04:54.690 --> 00:04:56.720
I just did this op-ed piece
for the "New York Times"

00:04:56.720 --> 00:04:58.370
where I talked about-- they
were asking me questions about,

00:04:58.370 --> 00:04:59.460
how did this start?

00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:02.960
And it hit me, my mother used
to take me to the projects

00:05:02.960 --> 00:05:05.480
with her to play
cards on the weekends.

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:07.870
And all these women would
sit around playing cards.

00:05:07.870 --> 00:05:10.310
Now these weren't your Sunday
morning proper bridge ladies

00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:10.940
playing bridge.

00:05:10.940 --> 00:05:13.490
These were cussing,
spitting, smoking, talking

00:05:13.490 --> 00:05:15.950
trash, strong black women.

00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:18.558
And they would sit around
me making all of these jokes

00:05:18.558 --> 00:05:19.100
and laughing.

00:05:19.100 --> 00:05:21.380
But the minute they start
talking about relationships,

00:05:21.380 --> 00:05:23.030
the whole room would get quiet.

00:05:23.030 --> 00:05:24.963
So I remembered as a
kid when my mother would

00:05:24.963 --> 00:05:26.630
be going through
things, I would imitate

00:05:26.630 --> 00:05:28.550
those women to make her laugh.

00:05:28.550 --> 00:05:31.020
So here I am all these years
later being able to do this.

00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:33.270
I didn't know that that was
like a master class for me

00:05:33.270 --> 00:05:35.360
as a little boy to
be able to do this.

00:05:35.360 --> 00:05:39.600
But where she started
was in that moment.

00:05:39.600 --> 00:05:45.650
But I had a show in
2000 at the theater

00:05:45.650 --> 00:05:48.740
in Chicago, the 79th and
[INAUDIBLE],, the Regal Theater.

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:51.883
And this particular actress
that I had been promoting

00:05:51.883 --> 00:05:52.800
was going to be there.

00:05:52.800 --> 00:05:54.133
She had a hit song on the radio.

00:05:54.133 --> 00:05:55.250
She was huge at the time.

00:05:55.250 --> 00:05:56.150
She didn't show up.

00:05:56.150 --> 00:05:58.567
So Madea was only supposed to
be on stage for five minutes

00:05:58.567 --> 00:06:00.260
after I seen Eddie
Murphy do the Klumps.

00:06:00.260 --> 00:06:02.330
I was doing two different
characters in the play.

00:06:02.330 --> 00:06:05.060
But when she didn't show up,
I had to say all of her lines

00:06:05.060 --> 00:06:07.763
and Madea's lines, and
the audience went crazy.

00:06:07.763 --> 00:06:08.930
And that's where it started.

00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:10.043
You were two.

00:06:10.043 --> 00:06:11.210
But that's where it started.

00:06:11.210 --> 00:06:11.500
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:12.360
That's where it started.

00:06:12.360 --> 00:06:12.680
KEN WALKER: Wow.

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:14.108
DE'ARRA TAYLOR:
That was the case.

00:06:14.108 --> 00:06:15.540
Wow.

00:06:15.540 --> 00:06:18.488
So my question is for
the "Madea Funeral,"

00:06:18.488 --> 00:06:20.780
was your whole thought behind
this movie and coming out

00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:23.960
with this movie and it being the
last movie that Madea would be

00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:26.810
in, was it like a trick to
get people to think like, hey,

00:06:26.810 --> 00:06:27.830
she's going to be dead?

00:06:27.830 --> 00:06:29.840
Because we saw the
movie yesterday.

00:06:29.840 --> 00:06:31.550
But before we
watched the movie, we

00:06:31.550 --> 00:06:32.660
thought like, she
was going to die,

00:06:32.660 --> 00:06:33.230
and duh, duh, duh, duh, duh.

00:06:33.230 --> 00:06:34.530
TYLER PERRY: Yeah,
I can't kill her.

00:06:34.530 --> 00:06:36.670
No, that would be like
killing a family member.

00:06:36.670 --> 00:06:38.220
Like it's a family
member to so many people,

00:06:38.220 --> 00:06:39.595
so no, I didn't
want to kill her.

00:06:39.595 --> 00:06:42.080
But I didn't know the funeral
was going to be the last one.

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:44.618
I just made a decision
after all of this

00:06:44.618 --> 00:06:46.160
and doing the final
tour, I was like,

00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:47.930
this is a good time
to put it to bed.

00:06:47.930 --> 00:06:50.675
Because part of the franchise
and everything-- what

00:06:50.675 --> 00:06:52.300
I was trying to do
is get to the studio

00:06:52.300 --> 00:06:54.510
down in Atlanta, which is--
if you haven't seen it,

00:06:54.510 --> 00:06:57.110
it's 330 acres, 12 soundstages.

00:06:57.110 --> 00:06:59.300
"Black Panther" reshoots
were done there.

00:06:59.300 --> 00:07:00.950
"The First Man" was shot there.

00:07:00.950 --> 00:07:02.370
"Rampage" was shot there.

00:07:02.370 --> 00:07:03.660
"Walking Dead" was shot there.

00:07:03.660 --> 00:07:05.660
So all these things
are shot at the studio.

00:07:05.660 --> 00:07:08.270
But that was the goal.

00:07:08.270 --> 00:07:10.523
So all these franchises,
everything that I was doing,

00:07:10.523 --> 00:07:11.690
I was working toward a goal.

00:07:11.690 --> 00:07:14.840
275,000 cars came through
the gates since I've opened.

00:07:14.840 --> 00:07:15.955
Working toward a goal.

00:07:15.955 --> 00:07:17.580
So now that the goal
has been achieved,

00:07:17.580 --> 00:07:19.870
now I feel like
I've met that level,

00:07:19.870 --> 00:07:21.868
now I'm free to just
do what I want to do.

00:07:21.868 --> 00:07:23.362
DE'ARRA TAYLOR: Oh yes.

00:07:23.362 --> 00:07:24.856
KEN WALKER: Whew!

