what I wanted to do.

00:41:45.270 --> 00:41:46.895
I knew I had something
that was special

00:41:46.895 --> 00:41:48.220
that was going to help people.

00:41:48.220 --> 00:41:50.630
Because my first show was about
adult survivors of child abuse.

00:41:50.630 --> 00:41:52.838
And I thought 1,200 people
would come the first week,

00:41:52.838 --> 00:41:54.130
and only 30 showed up.

00:41:54.130 --> 00:41:56.470
But out of that 30,
it helped somebody.

00:41:56.470 --> 00:41:57.570
So that was my focus.

00:41:57.570 --> 00:41:58.780
That was always my focus.

00:41:58.780 --> 00:42:02.020
So as long as I kept my
eye on what my focus was,

00:42:02.020 --> 00:42:04.240
the money came, everything
else fell in place.

00:42:04.240 --> 00:42:05.633
So don't deviate from the focus.

00:42:05.633 --> 00:42:08.050
There have been moments that
I've had to turn down things.

00:42:08.050 --> 00:42:10.175
I mean, there was this one
deal, I'll never forget.

00:42:10.175 --> 00:42:16.890
It was so good but for me,
it just didn't feel right.

00:42:16.890 --> 00:42:18.863
It was "Two and Half Men."

00:42:18.863 --> 00:42:20.530
Chuck Lorre, who did
"Two and Half Men,"

00:42:20.530 --> 00:42:23.410
"Roseanne--" we were working
on a sitcom together.

00:42:23.410 --> 00:42:25.490
And it just didn't
feel right for me.

00:42:25.490 --> 00:42:27.070
And I had this deal,
I was locked in.

00:42:27.070 --> 00:42:28.570
Everything in me,
I was just praying

00:42:28.570 --> 00:42:30.460
that the deal didn't happen,
because it didn't feel right.

00:42:30.460 --> 00:42:32.400
But I remember my agent's
oh, my god, you're

00:42:32.400 --> 00:42:34.192
going to make so much
money, so much money.

00:42:34.192 --> 00:42:35.870
But it just didn't feel right.

00:42:35.870 --> 00:42:38.590
So when the deal fell apart, I
was so happy and so relieved.

00:42:38.590 --> 00:42:40.670
Because out of that,
"House of Payne,"

00:42:40.670 --> 00:42:43.280
"The Have and Have Nots," "Meet
the Browns," all these shows

00:42:43.280 --> 00:42:43.780
were born.

00:42:43.780 --> 00:42:46.285
And the difference
is I own all of them.

00:42:46.285 --> 00:42:48.160
In that show, I wouldn't
have owned anything.

00:42:48.160 --> 00:42:48.940
[APPLAUSE]

00:42:48.940 --> 00:42:50.620
So that made the difference.

00:42:50.620 --> 00:42:53.590
So go with how you
feel about it, man.

00:42:53.590 --> 00:42:55.780
What does this feel like?

00:42:55.780 --> 00:42:56.890
Does it feel right?

00:42:56.890 --> 00:42:59.172
And if it doesn't feel
right, don't do it.

00:42:59.172 --> 00:43:01.380
No matter what it is, no
matter how much money it is.

00:43:01.380 --> 00:43:05.180
And I know it's hard for a
lot of people to go, hey,

00:43:05.180 --> 00:43:08.208
they just offered me $3 million,
and I got $2.50 in the bank.

00:43:08.208 --> 00:43:10.000
You think I'm not going
to take this money?

00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:12.470
But it's got to
be what you feel.

00:43:12.470 --> 00:43:14.620
Because had I taken
that show, my life

00:43:14.620 --> 00:43:15.850
would be very different.

00:43:15.850 --> 00:43:17.270
Ownership would
be very different.

00:43:17.270 --> 00:43:18.760
I would have never been
able to own the studio.

00:43:18.760 --> 00:43:21.302
I would never have been able to
hire all the people that I've

00:43:21.302 --> 00:43:23.830
hired and help all the people
and make as many millionaires

00:43:23.830 --> 00:43:24.400
as I have.

00:43:24.400 --> 00:43:27.160
Because I would have been
tied to someone else owning

00:43:27.160 --> 00:43:28.600
my intellectual property.

00:43:28.600 --> 00:43:30.350
So ownership is the key.

00:43:30.350 --> 00:43:31.080
Yeah, yeah.

00:43:31.080 --> 00:43:31.520
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:43:31.520 --> 00:43:32.937
TYLER PERRY: Thank
you, everybody.

00:43:32.937 --> 00:43:33.820
[APPLAUSE]

00:43:33.820 --> 00:43:35.670
Thank you.

